<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The local pointer 'timebase' is only used to read fields (timebase->freerun_time) and is never modified; it therefore could and should be declared as a pointer to a const-qualified type (const OS_timebase_internal_record_t *timebase). Declaring it non-const violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13.
</scenario>
